ly years of Louis XIII’s government have been insufficiently appreciated, and in the process throws light upon a dark, unpleasant corner of Richelieu’s personality often ignored by historians. As well as advanced students and historians of early modern France, this book should interest those specialising in the history of the European courts, power politics, patronage and printed pamphlet literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFavorites, RoyalzFrancevBiography. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  aCardinal Richelieu.  aConcini's murder.  aLouis XIII's government.  aOrder of Saint Esprit.  aProtestants.  aQueen Mother's revolt.  aanti-Luynes attack.  acharacter assassination.  acourt nobility.  aduc de Luynes.  afalconer.  amilitary order.  apamphlet attack.  aroyal ballets.  asiege of Montauban.1 aKettering, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130365423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130365/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles